<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <%- include('components/head.ejs'); -%>
        <title>Covaccine Scheduler</title>
        <style>
            .button{
                text-decoration: none; padding: 10px; position: relative; right: -40%;
            }
            @media only screen and (max-width: 1000px) {
                .button{
                    right: 0%;
                }
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body style="text-align: center;">
      <%- include('components/header.ejs'); -%>

      <div class="home">
          <div class="text left">
              <h1>Get your Vaccination Appointment Number and Date</h1>
              <a class="card icon-box button" href="/register"><h3><i>Register</i></h3></a>
          </div>
          <img class="img right" src="/img/covid.png" alt="covid">
      </div>
      
       <div class="info">
              <!-- <span>About</span> -->
              <p>
                Covaccine Scheduler is the digital solution for vaccination drive, it doesn't work on first come, first serve idea, rather it works on the idea "who needs vaccination first?". <br>
                Vaccination drive will be phase-wise, details of which are described below. <br>
                <strong> Phase 1 </strong> <br>
                <ul>
                <li>Healthcare Personnel.</li>
                <li>Frontline essential employees working in various government departments.</li>
                </ul>
                <strong> Phase 2 </strong> <br>
                <ul>
                <li>People aged 75 years or above because they are at high risk of hospitalization, illness, and death due to COVID-19.</ul>
                </ul>
                <strong> Phase 3 </strong> <br>
                <ul>
                  <li>People aged 65—74 years because they are at high risk of hospitalization, illness, and death due to COVID-19. </li>
                </ul>
                <strong> Phase 4 </strong> <br>
                <ul>
                  <li>People aged 16—64 years with underlying medical conditions which increase the risk of serious, life-threatening complications from COVID-19. </li>
                </ul>
                <strong> Phase 5 </strong>
                <ul>
                  <li>Other essential workers, such as people who work in transportation and logistics, food service, housing construction and finance, information technology, communications, energy, law, media, public safety, and public health.</li>
                </ul>
                <strong> Phase 6 </strong>
                <ul>
                  <li>Rest of the citizens.</li>
                </ul>
              </p>
            </div>

      <br><br>
